In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 6, 2012, as German-American Day in the United States. He acknowledges the contributions of German immigrants and their descendants to American society, highlighting their commitment to hard work, civic engagement, and family. The President emphasizes the strong alliance between the United States and Germany, noting the collaboration between the citizens of both nations in various fields such as entrepreneurship, innovation, education, and defense. He encourages all Americans to learn more about the history of German Americans and appreciate their contributions to the nation.